replies.body:
@Meddler this is a huge opportunity to finally introduce post-pick bans. It would add a lot of strategy and depth to League's champ select, especially for an esport that is only recently taking advantage of coaches and analysts. Having it be 3 bans each side, then 2 picks, then 2 bans each side and then the remaining 3 picks would be an incredible way to improve league of legends. Another thing this avoids is egregiously strong champions never being seen. If a champ has to get by 10 ban slots to reach picking phase when they're really strong, they're probably going to have a 100% ban rate and 0% pick rate. If they only have to make it past 6 like the current system, we will still see some pick rate of that champion despite the large number of bans.

Additionally this will let teams evolve their bans based on the picks. Enemy picked Jayce Nidalee, well let's ban Varus to disrupt their poke comp because we suspect that is their mid lane pick.

I really hope you guys extensively test some kind of banning system where some bans happen after some picks, it makes champ select so much more interesting. Right now I would say champ select in pro play is pretty stale.
